ations of a global music historiography, building on new models such as transnationalism, entangled histories, and reflexive globalization. The relationship between music and broader changes in society is placed at the center of attention and considered a pivotal music-historical dynamic.  afunded by FWF  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aMusic and globalization. 0aMusicxHistoriography. 4a20th Century. 4aAsia. 4aChina. 4aCultural History. 4aCultural Studies. 4aEntangled Histories. 4aGlobalization. 4aInterculturalism. 4aJapan. 4aKorea. 4aMusic. 4aMusicology. 4aTransnationalism. 7aMUSIC / History & Criticism.2bisacsh  a20th Century.  aAsia.  aChina.  aCultural History.  aCultural Studies.  aEntangled Histories.  aGlobalization.  aInterculturalism.  aJapan.  aKorea.  aMusic.  aMusicology.  aTransnationalism.1 aLaurence Sinclair Willis,.2 aFWFefunder.4fnd4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/fnd08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2021 Part 2z978311074335708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2021 Englishz978311075412408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2021z9783110753899oZDB-23-DKU08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript English Frontlist eBook-Package 2021z978311076731540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783839450956zOp